%section.skills.panel
  .wrap
    %header.section-header
      .padding
        %h1.beta.extra-bold-weight Skills
        %p.epsilon I'm a Front-end Developer with a keen eye for design, a desire to continually improve my abilities and over 4 years professional experience under my belt.
        %p.epsilon Click on the panels below to read a little about my core skill sets and approach to web development.
  .tabbed-content
    %ul.tabbed-content-nav{ role: "tablist" }
      %li{ role: "presentation" }
        = link_to "CSS", "#", role: "tab", class: "css"
      %li{ role: "presentation" }
        = link_to "HTML", "#", role: "tab", class: "html"
      %li{ role: "presentation" }
        = link_to "JavaScript", "#", role: "tab", class: "javascript"
      %li{ role: "presentation" }
        = link_to "Web standards", "#", role: "tab", class: "web-standards"
    .tabbed-content-body.clearfix
      %article.css.tabbed-content-tab
        .padding
          %h1.gamma.extra-bold-weight CSS
          .column-one
            %p.epsilon The art of presenting beautiful content for the web is something which still excites me to this day.
            %p CSS is the area of my job which always makes the biggest initial impact and it's for this reason that I take great care in making sure that my responsive builds look fantastic and feel intuitive&mdash;no matter what platform they're being viewed on.
            %p In my opinion, what's going on "under the hood" is just as important as what's presented in the browser, which is why I'm quite meticulous when it comes to organising my work and being as modular as possible. Spaghetti is good, but CSS spaghetti tastes bad.
            %p I have made great relationships with the designers I have worked with in the past and I'm always happy to provide guidance and constructive criticism where it's due in order to deliver a stunning* final product.
            %p.eta *exact level of stunningness dependent on design.
          .column-two
            %h2.epsilon My expertise at a glance:
            %ul
              %li CSS
              %li CSS3
              %li Sass
              %li Less
              %li Responsive web design
              %li Modular CSS
          .column-three
            %h2.epsilon Toolkit
            %ul
              %li= image_tag "toolkit/susy.png", alt: "Susy"
              %li= image_tag "toolkit/bourbon.png", alt: "Bourbon"
              %li= image_tag "toolkit/compass.png", alt: "Compass"
